Sep 26 2009 	Good location and value	I am just coming to the end of a one week stay at this hotel. It's my first time in Beijing but I spend a lot of time in hotels.I selected this hotel based solely on location as I knew I'd have a Saturday free at the end of my business trip.The location is excellent. Tian'anmen Square is a 3km walk (30 minutes) if you go down Wangfujing Dajie and along Dondchang'an Jie. The Forbidden City is 1.8km (20 minutes) if you take the short cut down Dong'anmen Dajie and either you can use the trolley round to Wumen Gate or walk. The walk is quite pleasant.Back to the hotel!I selected a club room which gives you access to the lounge on the 8th floor where a continental or mini-buffet breakfast is served daily 0630 and 1030 and cocktail hour between 1730 and 1930. It also gives you free local faxing. A fruit plate is brought in a couple of times a week. The mini bar allows 2 free Tsingtao, 2 free coke and 2 free sprites daily. Free local telephone calls and finally one shirt per day washed and pressed. The room itself is spacious with a desk area wireless or cable broadband at 120RMB per day (which appears to be the standard price in Europe). The king size bed was comfortable although on one side the mattress sagged ( a sign that they probably don't turn the mattresses at all and so should probably replace them more often). There is a walk in wardrobbe area which leads into a bathroom that is spacious and well lit. The bathroom has a medium sized bath and a separated shower. The TV has about 30 channels of which about 6 are in english and two are movie channels so you can watch some sport, catch the news or watch a movie.The room was mostly quiet, yes I could occasionally hear people above me or in adjoining rooms but no more than most rooms. The buffet breakfast in the main restaurant downstairs is OK but I have to admit I've never been a fan of buffet breakfasts anyway. I also had lunch one day in the same restaurant and wasn't particularly impressed. I had the clam chowder, nasi goreng and a tsingtao beer which came to 210RMB but the quality of the food wasn't great.The gym on the 9th floor is small. It has two treadmills, two bikes, a step machine, plenty of free weights and about half a dozen weight-lifting machines. I didn't try the sauna or steam rooms but they appeared to be fine. The swimming pool is small with probably only enough room for two people to swim lengths. It looks like the swimming cap rule has been dispensed with as I wasn't asked to wear one.The only other negative comment I could make is that one one day my complimentary beer wasn't restocked but I'm sure had I wanted some I could have rung down to get it restocked.The staff were friendly, fast, efficient, helpful and most spoke very good english.Would I stay here again? Absolutely.	
Aug 11 2009 	Excellent hotel in great location	Our first time in China and Beijing so keen to have comfortable stress free accomodation. Made an excellent choice with the Crowne Plaza on Wangfujing Street. 100 RMB taxi ride from airport. Check in was easy with reception staff who spoke English OK. Our rooms were reasonably large and nicely decorated with very comfortable king size beds. The large hotel atrium is stunning (absolutely no smell by the way!) with friendly drinks service and pianist in the evening. The ground floor &quot;Purple Bar&quot; is a bit dull and rather overshadowed by the atrium. The swimming pool is small but well maintained (swimming caps compulsory). Business centre has expensive internet access. The concierge staff were friendly and helpful. They quickly sorted out taxis and arranged a good deal for a day trip to the Great Wall.This is a 5/4 star hotel so don't be surprised it's expensive to use the bars and restaurants. We had hotel dinner one night which was nicely served and delicious. We ate breakfast most days in the Intime Lotte Department store 100 metres down the street where you can have great value freshly baked pastries. The location of this hotel is excellent. As first time visitors we wanted easy access to the major tourist sites. The hotel is on the main tourist shopping street and within 40 minute walk (or short taxi ride) of Tiananmen square and The Forbidden City. It was great to stroll directly from the hotel down the street to the bright lights and crazy night food markets. There is a subway station 500 metres away.There are very few faults with this hotel. We had a very comfortable stay and I would definitely recommend it to tourist visitors who want to be close to the action.	
