May 1 2009 	Good Choice in Beijing -- Great Location Excellent Breakfast Good Rooms	Last October we stayed at the Embassy Suites for 4 nights as a base to explore Beijing. There is a lot to like about this hotel! The rooms are American style with all the standard amenities, including queen size beds. We thoroughly enjoyed the very large breakfast buffet with multiple choices, fresh squeeze oj, and hand made omlettes (for us, it was included in our room rate). So overall, an excellent choice.We agree too, with some of the watch-outs of previous posters. First, be leary of the scantily clad women wandering the halls and elevators offering massage on the top floor. It didn't scare us as it is not the really bad thing we heard about in other hotels -- we just said 'no' and were left alone -- we only saw this on one night, Friday night. Also, the bellmen offer tourist services, but everything is marked up. You are better off using your guidebooks and booking on your own as English is spoken in Beijing and is not that bad (the rural areas, it can be more difficult). Also since the location is right in the middle of the Wafjung district, be prepared to be approached at night by a few shady characters offering prostitution. Again, it wasn't bad and cops were out -- we never felt not safe in this area of town. The location is the best in the city, with Tianamen and everything else in walking distance. Book here with the confidence of American luxury in a foreign local.	
