Sep 27 2007 	Great location	Booked this via Cathay Pacific holidays departing from HK, which was cheaper than we could've bought the flights and room separately on the net. We stayed two nights, then left Beijing, then returned for a night. Basically, this is a refurbished 4-star place in a great location. The rooms are of a good, rather than exceptional, standard. Ask for a room that looks onto the street, rather than internally into the atrium (see photo). I didn't hear any traffic noise (though could hear the TV from the next room in the morning). There are separate non-smoking and smoking floors. The gym is small and basic: two treadmills, two bikes and four machines. A bench press. Dumbells go up to 50 pounds. The pool is also small, but adequate, and there's also a steamroom and sauna. It'll do a basic workout but not much more. I thought the staff were helpful: they ensured the taxi drivers knew which destination we wanted to get to, and wrote it down for them; they gave accurate information about restaurants (e.g the Dadong restaurant, which is meant to have the best duck in town); they called our next hotel to find out where we were to be dropped off. The location is, as others have mentioned, excellent. Right on Wangfujing, so a 5 to 10 minute walk to the night market, the shops and Oriental Plaza (which is where the nearest subway stop is). It's about 20 minutes to Tiananmen Square or to the northern entrance to the Forbidden City. I think the place is well-situated and good value for money. That said, I think I'll treat myself to a more upmarket place next time in I'm in Beijing.	
